<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{4}{y}={55}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}{x}-{2}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{4}{y}={55}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={55}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{55}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{\left(\frac{{{55}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}\right)}+-{2}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{2}}{{-{{5}}}}\cdot{\left({55}\right)}-\frac{{2}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left({4}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{22}-{\left({1.6}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.6}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{24}--{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.6}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({1.6}+{\left(-{2}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.4}{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{2}}{{-{{0.4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{4}{\left({5}\right)}={55}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left({20}\right)}={55}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={55}-{\left({20}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{35}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>